column2: Have you ever had both of your tubes tied, cut, or removed? This procedure is often called a tubal ligation or tubal sterilization.
Have you ever had a hysterectomy, that is, surgery to remove your uterus?
Has (HUSBAND/PARTNER) ever had a vasectomy or any other operation that would make it impossible for him to father a baby in the future?
(If currently sexually active and not sterilized) The last time that you had sexual intercourse, did you or your partner use any method of contraception?
(If used contraception at last intercourse) What contraceptive method did you or your partner use?
column20: 6 = Female sterilizing operation, such as tubal sterilization and hysterectomy
column24: 10 = Calendar rhythm, Standard Days, or Cycle Beads method
column25: 11 = Safe period by temperature or cervical mucus test (Two Day, Billings Ovulation, or Sympto-thermal Method)
